Claude.ai SSE event taxonomy – The stream emits events of types message_start, content_block_start (text or tool_use), ping, content_block_delta (text_delta or input_json_delta), content_block_stop, message_delta, message_stop, and error. Each event carries a JSON payload; for example, message_start includes message id, model and token usage, content_block_start includes the block index and type, content_block_delta carries incremental text or partial JSON, and message_delta reports stop_reason and output token counts.

Translation to OpenAI‑compatible chunks – A state machine maps Anthropic events to the OpenAI chat.completions.chunk format: message_start.id → id, message_start.model → model; content_block_delta.text_delta.text → choices[0].delta.content; content_block_start.tool_use.id → choices[0].delta.tool_calls[i].id; content_block_start.tool_use.name → function.name; content_block_delta.input_json_delta.partial_json → function.arguments; message_delta.stop_reason → finish_reason; stream closure triggers the literal [DONE] token.

