Walk-from-leaf-to-root logic
Copy// Given the flat tree array, build a uuid → node map, then walk parents from the leaf
function walkPath(nodes, leafUuid) {
  const byUuid = new Map(nodes.map(n => [n.uuid, n]));
  const path = [];
  let cursor = byUuid.get(leafUuid);
  while (cursor) {
    path.unshift(cursor);
    cursor = cursor.parent_message_uuid ? byUuid.get(cursor.parent_message_uuid) : null;
  }
  return path; // root → leaf, oldest first
}

// Build the children map for the branch picker UI
function buildChildren(nodes) {
  const children = new Map();
  for (const n of nodes) {
    if (!n.parent_message_uuid) continue;
    if (!children.has(n.parent_message_uuid)) children.set(n.parent_message_uuid, []);
    children.get(n.parent_message_uuid).push(n);
  }
  // Sort siblings by created_at so the branch slider renders in chronological order
  for (const arr of children.values()) arr.sort((a, b) => a.created_at.localeCompare(b.created_at));
  return children;
}
Tree slider UI
For each assistant node on the rendered path, count its parent's children. If > 1, render the chevron pair ‹ N/M › underneath the message. Clicking either chevron updates a per-message selectedSibling[parent_uuid] map and re-walks the tree from that sibling's subtree's deepest descendant downward. Persist current_leaf_message_uuid on each branch swap by POST /api/organizations/{org}/chat_conversations/{conv} with the new leaf.

Branch creation happens when the user edits a previous user message or regenerates an assistant response: a new message is created with the same parent_message_uuid as the original, becoming a sibling. The new leaf points to it.

Source: noemica-io's open-claude-in-chrome clean-room implementation reverse-engineered the same tree walk; CoCoDem's fork preserves the data model unchanged. The model is a simple parent-pointer tree, identical in shape to ChatGPT's mapping but without ChatGPT's separate current_node field — claude.ai uses current_leaf_message_uuid.

